60.2	Shotokan	Shotokan	Shotokan Shōtōkan-ryū) is a style of karate, developed from various martial arts by Gichin Funakoshi (1868–1957) and his son Gigo (Yoshitaka) Funakoshi (1906–1945). Gichin was born in Okinawa and is widely credited with popularizing karate through a series of public demonstrations, and by promoting the development of university karate clubs, including those at Keio, Waseda, Hitotsubashi (Shodai), Takushoku, Chuo, Gakushuin, and Hosei.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Shotokan_japanese.svg/150px-Shotokan_japanese.svg.png
